# Portfolio JSON Structure

The [portfolio.json](mdc:src/data/portfolio.json) file contains all content for the portfolio website and should follow this structure:

## Basic Information
```json
{
  "basics": {
    "name": "Abdullah Saleh Robin",
    "title": "Senior Software Engineer",
    "summary": "...",
    "location": "...",
    "email": "...",
    "phone": "...",
    "profiles": [
      { "network": "LinkedIn", "url": "..." },
      { "network": "GitHub", "url": "..." }
      // Other profiles
    ]
  }
}
```

## Career Statistics
```json
{
  "statistics": {
    "yearsOfExperience": 5,
    "projectsDelivered": 20,
    "technologiesMastered": 15,
    "codeCommits": 2000
  }
}
```

## Skills and Expertise
```json
{
  "skills": [
    {
      "category": "Frontend",
      "items": [
        { "name": "React", "level": 90 },
        // Other frontend skills
      ]
    },
    // Other skill categories
  ]
}
```

## Experience
```json
{
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "...",
      "position": "...",
      "startDate": "...",
      "endDate": "...",
      "description": "...",
      "achievements": ["..."]
    }
    // Other experiences
  ]
}
```

## Projects
```json
{
  "projects": [
    {
      "title": "...",
      "description": "...",
      "technologies": ["..."],
      "imageUrl": "...",
      "projectUrl": "...",
      "githubUrl": "..."
    }
    // Other projects
  ]
}
```

## Education and Certifications
```json
{
  "education": [...],
  "certifications": [...]
}
```

Components should implement type checking and null checks when accessing this data structure.

